Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of cognitive mechanisms to support knowledge acquisition, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of metrics to rate rules and determine what to keep, consolidate, or forget is also related to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of the framework in a chess rule learning domain suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY).
